h3. Summary

When adding a quick-add button:

{code}
"jiraIssueContents": [
    {
        "icon": {
            "width": 0,
            "height": 0,
            "url": "/my_icon.svg"
        },
        "target": {
            "type": "web_panel",
            "url": "/hello-world"
        },
        "tooltip": {
            "value": "This is a tooltip. A hello world one"
        },
        "name": {
            "value": "Anne Issue Content Panel 0"
        },
        "key": "anne-issue-content-panel-0"
    }
],
{code}

and listening to the {{ISSUE_QUICK_ADD_CLICKED}} event:
{code}
AP.events.offAll('ISSUE_QUICK_ADD_CLICKED');
AP.events.on('ISSUE_QUICK_ADD_CLICKED', function(event) {
    // isNewToIssue is true if this is first time content panel being added to current issue.
    // isNewToIssue is false if content panel is already on issue view, and it is selected.
    console.log(`ISSUE_QUICK_ADD_CLICKED`, event);
});
{code}

The event is triggered multiple times on a single click of the quick-add button (see screenshot). Same goes for when target is a dialog and not a web_panel

*Observation*
- Multiple events are triggered on first click, succeeding ones fire single only
- Intermittent but easy to reproduce. Just refresh or try adding two {{jiraIssueContents}} and you should get at least 6 events

h3. Problem Definition
At this moment, when creating a date comparison condition in a workflow, admins can only use a fixed date.

When we need a condition where the transition is only available if the "Date Picker" custom field is set to less than 6 months from now in the future. Examples:

* Today is 09-12-2018. If the "Date Picker" is set to 11-12-2018, then the transition is *available*;
* Today is 09-12-2018. If the "Date Picker" is set to 04-12-2019, then the transition is *unavailable*;

This is not possible using conditions, right now.
 !Value Field Condition.png|thumbnail! 

h3. Suggested Solution
Add the ability for admins to create a date comparison condition based on a JQL search.
 !Future date.png|thumbnail! 

h3. Why this is important
This should enhance greatly the user experience.

h3. Workaround 
(*Please note*: At this moment, this workaround can be done only by Jira admins!)
We can add a *Date Compare Validator*, which has broader options for date comparisons. To achieve this:

# Type the *g* key twice on your keyboard (gg) or, as alternative, your *period* key ( *.* ), then *Projects*;
# Select the relevant project;
# Click *workflows*;
# Find the relevant workflow for the relevant issue type, then click the *Pencil icon* on your right corner;
# Select the relevant transition, then click *Validators*;
# Click *Add Validator*, select *Date Compare Validator*, then click *Add*;
# Configure the validator as needed, then click *Add*;
#* Perform steps 5 to 7 on all relevant transitions!
# Don't forget to publish the workflow draft!

 !Validator.png|thumbnail! 

 !Validator 2.png|thumbnail! 

The only drawback is that the transition will always be available (as we are not working with conditions), but Jira will throw an error with an understandable message on it.

 !Validator 3b.png|thumbnail!

